Phoenix Tower is a 27 level residential development sitting on 3442 square meters piece of land in Eko Atlantic, a new coastal city that is being built on Victoria Island adjacent to Lagos city, Nigeria. Also Read: Alexander Court Development in Ikoyi, Lagos, Nigeria This elegant tower provides a choice of brilliantly designed and well-proportioned 3 bedroom apartments, the largest of their kind in the new coastal city with modern home facilities and top-class finishes. The apartments are arranged from level 6 to 25 with 6 apartments on each floor.  The development also features 2 levels of penthouse villas, and amenities such as a swimming pool with adequate sitting area, a spa, a gym, and kids play area, a lounge, and a multi-purpose hall, amongst others. The project is developed by Arkland Properties and Investment, a leading and dynamic real estate and property management company, in partnership with Providus Bank Limited (PBL), is a Nigerian financial services provider, licensed as a commercial bank, by the Central Bank of Nigeria, the central bank and national banking regulator. Other key players in the project include Arkland Structures, Yasnas Engineering Ltd, SigmaSpec Electromechanical Ltd, Richard Eid, Otce/Vilner, and ITB Nigeria Limited.